<title>BULGARIA: Bulgaria coal mine managers sacked after explosion.</title>
<headline>Bulgaria coal mine managers sacked after explosion.</headline>
<dateline>SOFIA 1997-06-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Bulgarian government has sacked the management of a coal mine where 11 miners were injured in a methane explosion on Monday, state news agency BTA said.</p>
<p>It quoted Deputy Prime Minister Evgeni Bakardzhiev as saying more than 20 miners had been killed at Bobov Dol mine in the past seven or eight years and its safety record was unacceptable.</p>
<p>State radio said a new director was expected to take office later on Tuesday at the mine, 70 km (42 miles) west of Sofia.</p>
<p>Monday's gas explosion occurred when a ventilator was switched on after a power cut. Four miners who suffered burns were still in a serious condition, the radio said.</p>
